Make the script executable with 
chmod +x script_name.sh

"🚀 **Automated Repository Management Script** 🚀"
    "This script automates the process of managing repositories. It can:"
  "  - Remove existing cloned repositories"
  "  - Clone fresh copies from GitLab"
  "  - Checkout a specific branch and run 'make gen'"
    "Usage: $0 [OPTIONS]"
    "Options:"
  "  -r, --remove      🔴 Remove existing repositories"
  "  -c, --clone       🌍 Clone repositories from GitLab"
  "  -g, --generate    ⚙️  Checkout branch and run 'make gen' in each repository"
  "  -e, --extra       ⚙️  Run 'make gen.base' only"
  "  -a, --all         🚀 Run all steps (remove → clone → checkout & build)"
  "  -h, --help        📖 Show this help message"
    "Examples:"
  "  ./common_clone_fix.sh --remove          # Remove old repositories"
  "  ./common_clone_fix.sh --clone           # Clone repositories only"
  "  ./common_clone_fix.sh --generate        # Checkout branch and run 'make gen'"
  "  ./common_clone_fix.sh --extra           # Run 'make gen.base' only"
  "  ./common_clone_fix.sh --all             # Run everything"
    "✨ Created for efficient repo management!"

